NAME
    ping - send requests to a target in a loop

SYNOPSIS
    ping [options] <target>

DESCRIPTION
    Sends HTTP requests to a target and displays response times.
    Runs until interrupted or count is reached.

    Targets:
    - /health           Ping local API health endpoint
    - /api/data/users   Ping any local API path
    - http://example.com  Ping an external URL

OPTIONS
    -c <count>
        Stop after sending count requests. Default: infinite.

    -i <interval>
        Wait interval seconds between pings. Default: 1.
        Minimum: 0.1

EXAMPLES
    ping /health
        Ping the local health endpoint every second

    ping -c 5 /health
        Ping 5 times and exit

    ping -i 2 http://google.com
        Ping Google every 2 seconds

    ping /health > /var/log/ping.log &
        Run in background, log to file

OUTPUT
    64 bytes from localhost: seq=1 time=12.3ms
    64 bytes from localhost: seq=2 time=8.1ms

    --- localhost ping statistics ---
    2 packets transmitted, 2 received, 0.0% packet loss
    rtt min/avg/max = 8.1/10.2/12.3 ms

SEE ALSO
    ps, kill, sleep
